node.text: Such a rad time with an awesome group of peoples. The @GridExperience definitely sets the bar (and sets it pretty high) for me when it comes to indoor karting. Combine that with a this crew of friends and fam: Jeremy McGrath, Sage Kotsenburg, Zak Hale, Davey Coombs (founder of Racer X), Zac Mertens (of Hoonigan Racing), etc. - plus Jett and Hunter Lawrence were two of the top three fastest of the night (same positions as they finished in the 250 Main of the Supercross race this past weekend!). Jeremy’s daughter (Rhowan) and my daughter (Lia) both had two of the top lap five times also (yep, we’re proud Dads!). Good times!

node.title: Rad time karting at The Grid Experience with friends and fam.

node.text: Onboard action from today on Stage 2: “Plug Mill” (Reverse), in the @OlympusRally. 6.76 miles of fast gravel roads weaving through sections of dense, almost black forest and patches of completely clear cut land. With only one proper day of testing before @AlexGelsomino and I show up this weekend to the @OlympusRally (3rd round of the @ARA_Rally Championship) it will be interesting to see how quickly I can get fully comfortable in it and run at full tilt. But so far, the car looks (livery by @ItsALiving) and feels (built and prepped by Vermont SportsCar) great! Check out this week's episode on my YouTube channel (link in bio) for the livery reveal, and to hear about all our plans for a wild year! #gravelslayingaction

node.text: Here’s another AINT CARE moment from the vault: @AlexGelsomino and I lost our front right side wheel midway through Stage 3 (of Oregon Trail Rally in 2013) due to a freak mechanical failure. We kept the hammer down and finished that stage, and then continued on to run another full stage on just 3 wheels, rather than settling for a DNF. We finished the race 2nd overall - all because we were able to drive through this #AINTCARE situation!

node.text: AIN’T CARE, rally cross example: after qualifying first, winning each of the heats, and leading the first 5 laps of the Final in the 2012 GRC race in Las Vegas, the ECU/control panel in my race car caught fire. I continued the race for as long as I could, but the fumes from the fire were starting to burn my lungs. I led and raced for as long as I could but eventually had to stop. I truly tried to AIN’T CARE as long as I could, but wasn’t willing to die for the win. 🤷‍♂️ #AINTCARE #pressonregardless

node.title: AIN’T CARE - GRC Las Vegas - FIRE

node.text: Enjoy this dual-onboard video from Stage 7 (Asbridge Hollow) from this weekend’s Rally In The 100 Acre Wood. @AlexGelsomino and I were fastest on this stage to start off Saturday morning. node.text: The first stage is usually one of the more difficult of any rally, simply due to nerves and refamiliarization with the road surface and race car. The Concord Pond stage is easily one of the best stages in the ARA championship, and with @alexgelsomino and I being 2nd on the road - along with rain the night before the race - meant that we raced it with near-perfect conditions. Enjoy this fun and fast section from the stage, where we managed to set the 2nd fastest time overall.

node.text: Big airtime yesterday!! @alexgelsomino and I are currently sitting 2nd overall after 5 stages going into day 2 here at the New England Forest Rally. The top 5 cars are separated by only 30 seconds - so with 9 stages left, and an absolutely stacked line up of drivers, it’s going to be a close battle for the podium spots.

node.text: My Hoonigan Racing teammate, @jaxredline, has finished his first day EVER of racing rally in 8th place!! Great day of racing for this 16-year-old off-road racing prodigy, here at the New England Forest Rally! The field here is stacked with seasoned drivers and Jax managed to consistently get faster throughout the day. And, he has kept my Cossie V2 in the middle of the road and in perfect condition. Day 2 starts early this morning. Wish him luck! #BlockEscortCossieV2 #NEFR

node.text: @jaxredline is getting real comfortable behind the seat of the Cossie V2.  He got a chance to get some REAL seat time on the gravel stages at @teamoneil rally school prior to this weekend’s race at New England Forest Rally.  He’s learning fast too!

node.text: My wife Lucy is racing her Fiesta R2 in three American Rally Association races this year, starting this weekend with the New England Forest Rally… so, we had to make her a new Hoonigan livery (designed by Hoonigan fan, @camilleyetter), right?? Here it is, in all its FWD wheel-spinning glory. I like.

node.text: ‘90’s Cossie & ‘21 Subaru STI. Two rad rally beasts from two different eras - and both being raced this weekend at the New England Forest Rally featuring my Hoonigan Racing livery by It’s A Living! Off-road prodigy @jaxredline is making a go at rally for his first time (with experienced rally co-driver @hoffbrinkle) and @alexgelsomino and I are going for our 2nd win at this race. What’re your predictions?? #BlockEscortCossieV2 #SubaruSTI #NEFR
